  framework also raises the question: can traditions be understood as conventions? Or do they
  require different conceptual resources?

  POSITION: Analytic philosophy of language and action. Convention as coordination equilibrium
  based on common knowledge and mutual expectations, distinguished from tradition by arbitrariness
