  goals.

  RELEVANCE: Tuomela's we-mode framework provides conceptual resources for understanding how
  traditions are collectively sustained. If traditions are social practices requiring collective
  acceptance, then participants must adopt we-mode attitudes: acting as members of the tradition-
  bearing community rather than as isolated individuals. This helps explain tradition's normative
  force and its persistence across individual lifecycles. Tuomela's framework connects tradition
  to social ontology debates about collective intentionality and raises questions about what
  kind of collective acceptance is required for tradition.

  POSITION: Social ontology emphasizing collective acceptance and we-mode sociality. Social
  practices sustained through participants acting as group members and collectively accepting
  constitutive norms.
  },
  keywords = {Tuomela, social-practices, collective-acceptance, we-mode, Low}
}

@incollection{salice2012social,
  author = {Salice, Alessandro},
