  RELEVANCE: This comprehensive study clarifies MacIntyre's complex and often misunderstood position on tradition. It shows how MacIntyre defends tradition not as static inheritance but as dynamic framework for inquiry that develops through internal criticism and external engagement. Essential for understanding sophisticated philosophical defenses of tradition that avoid both relativism and foundationalism.

