  RELEVANCE: This work attempts to bridge the gap between tradition-based approaches (MacIntyre) and critical theory (Frankfurt School), showing potential synthesis rather than mere opposition. Important for seeing how critiques of Enlightenment rationalism from different quarters (virtue ethics and critical Marxism) might complement each other. Addresses whether tradition-constituted rationality can accommodate the critical and emancipatory aims that Habermas finds lacking in Gadamer.

